Columbia River Steelhead SAR estimates and forecasts

Thomas Buehrens

Page Last Updated: 02/03/2023.

Overview

This code uses summer steelhead PIT tag counts and adult counts from Bonneville Dam to estimate:

  1. smolt to adult survival (measured from Bonneville Dam, out to sea, and back to Bonneville Dam)
  2. adult ocean age composition (assuming 2 age classes)
  3. runsize at Bonneville Dam

Different PIT tag datasets can be used to estimate smolt to adult survival and age composition (e.g., for Upper Columbia or Snake or Lower Columbia), each of which is then used to estimate overall runsize at Bonneville. Snake River data generally results in the most precise adult runsize estimates and forecasts at Bonneville because it is the greatest component of the total runsize and is therefore more predictive of the total abundance.

Read and organize data

Here we will read in a .csv of PIT tag data generated from a query here, and we will directly call adult counts generated from a query here. The date range for the adult query will be restricted to 6/1-11/30 (corresponding to TAC dates for upriver summer steelhead counts) to generate an approximate index of the summer-run portion of the count.

dat<-read_csv("https://www.cbr.washington.edu/dart/cs/php/rpt/pit_sar_esu.php?queryType=year&proj=BON&esu_type=SR_Sthd&rt=A&age=all&grouptype=basin&csvOnly=1")%>%
  dplyr::select(year,juvCount,ocean1Count,ocean2Count)%>%
  mutate(Pop="SNA")%>%
  dplyr::rename(rel=juvCount,`1`=ocean1Count,`2`=ocean2Count)%>%
  dplyr::filter(grepl("2",year))%>%
  mutate(year=as.numeric(year))%>%
  dplyr::filter(if(month(Sys.Date()) < 12) year < (year(Sys.Date())-1) else(year<year(Sys.Date())))%>%
  mutate(`2` = ifelse(year==year(Sys.Date())-2 & month(Sys.Date()) < 12, NA,`2`))%>%
  mutate(rel=as.integer(rel),`99`=as.integer(rel-`1`-`2`),pop_stan=as.integer(factor(Pop)),year_stan=as.integer(year-min(year)+1))%>%
  pivot_longer(cols=c(`1`,`2`,`99`),values_to = "det",names_to = "age_stan")%>%
  mutate(age_stan=as.integer(age_stan))%>%
  filter(!is.na(det))

dat2<-read_csv("http://www.cbr.washington.edu/dart/cs/php/rpt/adult_annual.php?sc=1&outputFormat=csv&proj=BON&startdate=6%2F1&enddate=11%2F30")%>%
  filter(Year>min(dat$year+1))%>%
  dplyr::select(Year,Steelhead)


dat3<-read_table("http://www.o3d.org/npgo/npgo.php",skip=29,col_names=F,comment="#")%>%
  filter(!is.na(X2))%>%
  dplyr::rename(year=X1,Month=X2,NPGO=X3)%>%
  mutate(year=as.numeric(year))%>%
  group_by(year)%>%
  add_tally()%>%
  #filter(!Month>6)%>% #use only spring (Jan-June) NPGO
  #filter(!n < 12)%>% #use only complete years
  group_by(year)%>%
  dplyr::summarise(mean_NPGO=mean(NPGO))

stan_dat<-dat%>%
  dplyr::select(obs_pop=pop_stan,
                obs_yr=year_stan,
                obs_age=age_stan,
                rel=rel,
                det=det
                )%>%
  as.list()%>%
  mutate(data_yrs=length(unique(obs_yr)),
         pops=length(unique(obs_pop)),
         obs=length(rel),
         forecast_yrs=1,
         ry_adults_obs = matrix(rep(dat2$Steelhead,pops),ncol=length(unique(dat$Pop)))
         )

dat3<-dat3%>%
  filter(year>=min(dat$year) & year <= max(dat$year+stan_dat$forecast_yrs))%>%
  dplyr::rename(Year=year)%>%
  mutate(X2 = ifelse(Year%%2==0,1,0))

stan_dat$NPGO<-dat3%>%
  dplyr::select(mean_NPGO)%>%
  unlist()

stan_dat$X2 = dat3%>%
  dplyr::select(X2)%>%
  unlist()


dat%>%
  dplyr::select(year,Pop,rel,det,age_stan)%>%
  dplyr::rename(`Smolt detections @ BON` = rel, `Adult detections @ BON` = det, age = age_stan, Population = Pop, `Outmigration Year` = year )%>%
  mutate(age = ifelse(age == 99,"Not Detected As Adult",paste0("Ocean Age ",age," detections @ BON")))%>%
  filter(age!="Not Detected As Adult")%>%
  pivot_wider(id_cols=c(`Outmigration Year`, Population, `Smolt detections @ BON`), names_from=age, values_from=`Adult detections @ BON`)%>%
  kbl(caption = "Table 1. Raw PIT Tag Data",digits =3)%>%
  kable_classic(full_width = F, html_font = "Cambria")

Stan Model

This section shows the Stan model code for estimating SAR, age composition, and run-size using PIT tag data, dam adult counts, and environmental covariates (e.g., NPGO).

processFile("models/Columbia_SAR_v2.stan")
## data{ 
##   int data_yrs; //years of PIT tag data 
##   int forecast_yrs; //years to forecast SAR 
##   int pops; //number of different populations we have PIT tag data for 
##   int obs; //number of PIT tag SAR observations  
##   int obs_yr[obs]; //year index for PIT tag SAR observations 
##   int obs_age[obs]; //age index for PIT tag SAR observations 
##   int obs_pop[obs]; //population index for PIT tag SAR observations 
##   int det[obs]; //number of smolt PIT tags detected passing BON going downstream 
##   int rel[obs]; //number of adult PIT tags detected passing BON going upstream 
##   int ry_adults_obs[data_yrs-1,pops]; //Bonneville Dam adult count 
##   vector[data_yrs + forecast_yrs] NPGO; //NPGO for outmigration years and forecast years 
##   vector[data_yrs + forecast_yrs] X2; //second covariate 
## } 
## transformed data{ 
##   int yrs = data_yrs + forecast_yrs; 
## } 
## parameters{ 
##   vector[pops] b1; 
##   vector[pops] b2; 
##  
##   vector<lower=0,upper=1>[pops] mu_SAR; 
##   vector<lower=-1,upper=1>[pops] phi_SAR; 
##   vector<lower=0>[pops] sigma_SAR; 
##   matrix[yrs,pops] eps_SAR; 
##  
##   vector<lower=0,upper=1>[pops] mu_p_OA1; 
##   vector<lower=-1,upper=1>[pops] phi_p_OA1; 
##   vector<lower=0>[pops] sigma_p_OA1; 
##   matrix[yrs,pops] eps_p_OA1; 
##    
##   vector<lower=0>[pops] smolts_0; 
##   matrix[yrs-1,pops] eps_smolts; 
##    
##   vector<lower=0>[pops]sigma_tot; 
##   vector<lower=0,upper=1>[pops] p_smolts; 
##  
## } 
## transformed parameters{ 
##   matrix<lower=0,upper=1>[yrs,pops] SAR; 
##   matrix[yrs,pops] SAR_resid; 
##   matrix<lower=0,upper=1>[yrs,pops] p_OA1; 
##   matrix[yrs,pops] p_OA1_resid; 
##   matrix<lower=0>[yrs,pops] smolts; 
##   matrix<lower=0>[yrs-1,pops] ry_adults; 
##   matrix<lower=0,upper=1>[yrs-1,pops] ry_p_OA1; 
##   vector<lower=0>[pops] sigma_disp; 
##   vector<lower=0>[pops] sigma_smolts; 
##    
##   for(p in 1:pops){ 
##     sigma_smolts[p] = sqrt(p_smolts[p] * square(sigma_tot[p])); 
##     sigma_disp[p] = sqrt((1-p_smolts[p]) * square(sigma_tot[p])); 
##   } 
##    
##   SAR_resid[1,] =  eps_SAR[1,] .* to_row_vector(sigma_SAR[1:pops]) ./ sqrt(1-to_row_vector(square(phi_SAR))); 
##   p_OA1_resid[1,] =  eps_p_OA1[1,] .* to_row_vector(sigma_p_OA1[1:pops]) ./ sqrt(1-to_row_vector(square(phi_p_OA1))); 
##   smolts[1,] = to_row_vector(smolts_0 .* rep_vector(1e7,pops)); 
##    
##   for(y in 2:yrs){ 
##     SAR_resid[y,1:pops] = to_row_vector(phi_SAR[1:pops]) .* SAR_resid[1,1:pops] + eps_SAR[y,1:pops] .* to_row_vector(sigma_SAR[1:pops]); 
##     p_OA1_resid[y,1:pops] = to_row_vector(phi_p_OA1[1:pops]) .* p_OA1_resid[1,1:pops] + eps_p_OA1[y,1:pops] .* to_row_vector(sigma_p_OA1[1:pops]); 
##     smolts[y,] = exp(log(smolts[y-1,]) + eps_smolts[y-1,] .* to_row_vector(sigma_smolts)); 
##   }

##   for(p in 1:pops){ 
##     SAR_resid[1:yrs,p] = SAR_resid[1:yrs,p] - mean(SAR_resid[1:yrs,p]);//constrain SAR resids to have zero mean

## } 
## model{ 
##   //priors 
##   b1 ~ normal(0,10); 
##   b2 ~ normal(0,10); 
##  
##  
##   mu_SAR ~ beta(1,1); 
##   phi_SAR ~ std_normal(); 
##   sigma_SAR ~ std_normal(); 
##   to_vector(eps_SAR) ~ std_normal(); 
##  
##   mu_p_OA1 ~ beta(1,1); 
##   phi_p_OA1 ~ std_normal(); 
##   sigma_p_OA1 ~ std_normal(); 
##   to_vector(eps_p_OA1) ~ std_normal(); 
##    
##   smolts_0 ~ lognormal(0,0.5); 
##   to_vector(eps_smolts) ~ std_normal(); 
##    
##   sigma_tot ~ std_normal(); 
##   p_smolts ~ beta(1,1); 
##   //likelihoods

##     if(obs_age[i]==1){ 
##       det[i] ~ poisson(rel[i] * SAR[obs_yr[i],obs_pop[i]] * p_OA1[obs_yr[i],obs_pop[i]]); 
##     } 
##     if(obs_age[i]==2){ 
##       det[i] ~ poisson(rel[i] * SAR[obs_yr[i],obs_pop[i]] * (1-p_OA1[obs_yr[i],obs_pop[i]])); 
##     } 
##     if(obs_age[i]==99){ 
##       det[i] ~ poisson(rel[i] * (1-SAR[obs_yr[i],obs_pop[i]])); 
##     } 
##   } 
##   for(y in 1:(data_yrs-1)){ 
##     for(p in 1:pops){ 
##       //ry_adults_obs[y,p] ~ neg_binomial(ry_adults[y,p],1/square(sigma_disp)); 
##       ry_adults_obs[y,p] ~ lognormal(log(ry_adults[y,p]),sigma_disp[p]); 
##       //ry_adults_obs[y,p] ~ poisson(ry_adults[y,p]); 
##     } 
##   } 
## } 
## generated quantities{ 
##   //int ry_adults_pred[yrs-1,pops];

Fit model to PIT tag data

This section of code fits the data to the statistical model using Stan software: (link).

if(!file.exists("results/fit.RDS")){
model<-stan_model("models/Columbia_SAR_v2.stan")
fit<-sampling(model,
              data=stan_dat,
              cores=4,
              chains=4,
              iter=2000,
              warmup=1000
              ,control=list(adapt_delta=0.999,max_treedepth=12)
              )
write.csv(summary(fit)$summary,"results/summary.csv")
saveRDS(fit,"results/fit.RDS")
}else{
  fit<-readRDS("results/fit.RDS")
}

sampler_params <- get_sampler_params(fit, inc_warmup = FALSE)
divergences <- sapply(sampler_params, function(x) sum(x[, "divergent__"]))
print(paste0("Number of divergent transitions: ",sum(divergences)))

SAR Results by outmigration year

dim<-ifelse(stan_dat$pops>1,3,2)
results<-melt(apply(extract(fit)$SAR,c(2:max(3,dim)),function(x) quantile(x,prob=c(0.025,0.25,0.5,0.75,0.975))))%>%
  as_tibble()%>%
  mutate(Var3ifelse(stan_dat$pops>1,Var3,1))%>%
  dplyr::rename(Q=Var1,Year=Var2,Population=Var3)%>%
  mutate(Population=ifelse(Population==1,"Snake River DPS","Upper Columbia River DPS"),Year=Year+min(dat$year)-1)%>%
  pivot_wider(id_cols = c("Year","Population"),names_from = Q,values_from = value)

p<-ggplot(results,aes(x=Year,y=`50%`,fill=Population,color=Population))+
  geom_ribbon(mapping=aes(ymin=`2.5%`,ymax=`97.5%`),alpha=0.25,color=NA)+
  geom_ribbon(mapping=aes(ymin=`25%`,ymax=`75%`),alpha=0.25,color=NA)+
  geom_line()+
  ylab("H + W Steelhead SAR by outmigration year (Bonneville to Bonneville)")+
  theme_bw()
print(p)

SAR to adult ratio

This section shows estimates of the ratio of adult abundance to SAR. If using SAR and adult data from the same population, this is a direct estimate of smolt abundnace. If using SAR from one population to estimate adult abundance of another, this is a “surrogate of smolt abundance” but may be biased r

results<-melt(apply(extract(fit)$smolts,c(2:dim),function(x) quantile(x,prob=c(0.025,0.25,0.5,0.75,0.975))))%>%
  as_tibble()%>%
  mutate(Var3=ifelse(stan_dat$pops>1,Var3,1))%>%
  dplyr::rename(Q=Var1,Year=Var2,Population=Var3)%>%
  mutate(Population=ifelse(Population==1,"Snake River DPS","Upper Columbia River DPS"),Year=Year+min(dat$year)-1)%>%
  pivot_wider(id_cols = c("Year","Population"),names_from = Q,values_from = value)

p<-ggplot(results,aes(x=Year,y=`50%`,fill=Population,color=Population))+
  geom_ribbon(mapping=aes(ymin=`2.5%`,ymax=`97.5%`),alpha=0.25,color=NA)+
  geom_ribbon(mapping=aes(ymin=`25%`,ymax=`75%`),alpha=0.25,color=NA)+
  geom_line()+
  ylab("H + W smolts abundance by outmigration year at Bonneville")+
  theme_bw()
print(p)

Effects of NPGO and a Pink Salmon even-odd year indicator variable on marine survival

NPGO_coef<-tibble(data.frame(extract(fit)$b1))%>%
  pivot_longer(cols = everything())%>%
  mutate(Var2=ifelse(stan_dat$pops>1,Var2,1))%>%
  dplyr::rename(Population=Var2,NPGO_coef=value)%>%
  mutate(Population=ifelse(Population==1,"Snake River DPS","Upper Columbia River DPS"))%>%
  dplyr::select(NPGO_coef,Population)
  
p<-ggplot(NPGO_coef,aes(x=NPGO_coef,fill=Population),color=NA)+
  geom_density()+
  facet_wrap(~Population,ncol=2)+
  ylab("Effect of NPGO on SAR")+
  theme_bw()+
  xlim(-1*max(NPGO_coef$NPGO_coef),max(NPGO_coef$NPGO_coef))+
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0)
print(p)
